{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f90f672-b73a-4752-af4a-0c07fe23ed89","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill is for *collecting* dumps (not analyzing), so let me help you directly.\n\nHere's how to analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze` (recommended for managed .NET)\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\n### Option 2: `lldb` with SOS (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core /path/to/your.dmp\n# then: clrstack, pe, etc.\n```\n\n### Option 3: WinDbg (Windows dumps)\nLoad with SOS extension (`.loadby sos coreclr`), then use the same SOS commands.\n\n---\n\n**To get started, could you share:**\n1. Where is your `.dmp` file located?\n2. Is it from .NET Framework or modern .NET (Core/5+)?\n3. Do you have `dotnet-dump` or `lldb` available?\n\nI can run the analysis commands for you if the dump is accessible in this environment.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"35261428-6439-48b5-906f-5bae62404557","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I don't see a specific skill for analyzing .dmp files. The \"dump-collect\" skill is specifically for *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them. Let me help the user directly with guidance on analyzing the dump.\n\nLet me check what tools are available in the environment first.","outputTokens":496,"requestId":"DA03:3F1DAE:70E1C51:799B201:6A03DA52"},"id":"10b93159-86b2-46d4-92